<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[189,1399,645,882]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="C.Chr., 1934 (C.Presl)" authorityName="C.Chr., 1934 (C.Presl)" box="[316,507,645,671]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Sphaerocionium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[316,507,645,671]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Sphaerocionium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is clearly distinct in the archipelago with two species characterized by lamina covered by a dense indumentum (see 
<figureCitation box="[716,809,680,706]" captionStart="Fig. 2" captionStartId="3.[189,232,1642,1668]" captionTargetBox="[229,1359,265,1603]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[229,1359,265,1603]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Illustration of representative descriptors and states used in the Xper database (see Appendix 1). A. Hymenophyllum hirsutum (L.) Sw., typical bilabiate sori (S) without a developed base, fully hairy lamina with pedunculated brown trichomes (see inset). B. Didymoglossum robinsonii (Hook. ex Baker) Copel., false veins (FV) parallel but not connected to true veins (TV) and marginal dark trichomes clustered here by 6 (see inset). C. Crepidomanes inopinatum (Pic. Serm.) J. P. Roux, typical trichomanoid sori (S) with a developed tubular base, lips are here dilated as a collar. D. Didymoglossum rotundifolium (Bonap.) J. P. Roux, false veins (FV) parallel but not connected to true veins (TV) and continuous submarginal false vein (smFV), here the one-cell thick lamina appears well translucent. E. Crepidomanes bipunctatum (Poir.) Copel., false veins more or less continuous and parallel to margins (mFV) and not connected to true veins (TV). F. Hymenophyllum sibthorpioides (Bory ex Willd.) Mett. ex Kuhn, bilabiate sori (S) with toothed margins. Photographs by A. H. Saïd." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/896405/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). By contrast, all other Comorian 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sm. (Smith" authorityYear="1793" box="[1206,1398,680,706]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Hymenophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1206,1398,680,706]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Hymenophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species display glabrous lamina margins. Furthermore, the two Comorian 
<taxonomicName authority="C.Chr., 1934 (C.Presl)" authorityName="C.Chr., 1934 (C.Presl)" box="[1103,1294,715,741]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Sphaerocionium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1103,1294,715,741]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Sphaerocionium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, 
<taxonomicName box="[189,491,750,776]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Hymenophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirsutum">
<emphasis box="[189,491,750,776]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Hymenophyllum hirsutum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) Sw. and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Desv., Memoires de la Societe" authorityYear="1827" box="[643,782,750,776]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Hymenophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capillare">
<emphasis box="[643,782,750,776]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">H. capillare</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are easily distinguished from each other: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Desv., Memoires de la Societe" authorityYear="1827" box="[1260,1399,750,776]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Hymenophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capillare">
<emphasis box="[1260,1399,750,776]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">H. capillare</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
usually has wingless stipes and rachis (except in dwarf forms exhibiting winged rachis, at least in their upper part) while 
<taxonomicName box="[396,534,821,847]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Hymenophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirsutum">
<emphasis box="[396,534,821,847]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">H. hirsutum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
always bears a developed wing all along the stipes and rachis. In addition, lamina hairs are pedunculated in 
<taxonomicName box="[577,717,856,882]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Hymenophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirsutum">
<emphasis box="[577,717,856,882]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">H. hirsutum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<figureCitation box="[780,871,856,882]" captionStart="Fig. 2" captionStartId="3.[189,232,1642,1668]" captionTargetBox="[229,1359,265,1603]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[229,1359,265,1603]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Illustration of representative descriptors and states used in the Xper database (see Appendix 1). A. Hymenophyllum hirsutum (L.) Sw., typical bilabiate sori (S) without a developed base, fully hairy lamina with pedunculated brown trichomes (see inset). B. Didymoglossum robinsonii (Hook. ex Baker) Copel., false veins (FV) parallel but not connected to true veins (TV) and marginal dark trichomes clustered here by 6 (see inset). C. Crepidomanes inopinatum (Pic. Serm.) J. P. Roux, typical trichomanoid sori (S) with a developed tubular base, lips are here dilated as a collar. D. Didymoglossum rotundifolium (Bonap.) J. P. Roux, false veins (FV) parallel but not connected to true veins (TV) and continuous submarginal false vein (smFV), here the one-cell thick lamina appears well translucent. E. Crepidomanes bipunctatum (Poir.) Copel., false veins more or less continuous and parallel to margins (mFV) and not connected to true veins (TV). F. Hymenophyllum sibthorpioides (Bory ex Willd.) Mett. ex Kuhn, bilabiate sori (S) with toothed margins. Photographs by A. H. Saïd." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/896405/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
) and not pedunculated in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Desv., Memoires de la Societe" authorityYear="1827" box="[1175,1315,856,882]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Hymenophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capillare">
<emphasis box="[1175,1315,856,882]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">H. capillare</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
